headline: AT&T's Dividend Yield Gap With 10-Year Treasury Yield Increases Rapidly
summary: AT&T's modest yield, limited growth drivers, and potential capex headwinds make it less attractive for long-term investors. Read more on T stock here.

headline: This Dividend Stock Is Up 4 Times More Than the S&P 500 in the Past Year. Here's Why I'm Loading Up On It.
summary: AT&T expects its free cash flow for 2025 to be around twice what it will pay in dividends.  AT&T's fiber business will drive its next phase of growth.  The telecom industry operates as a virtual oligopoly because of the high barriers to entry and the scale needed to compete.
